I haven't done any mathematical tests, but I simply have noticed that when I charm-kite with my full charisma gear I tend to get fewer resists and more of my charms last full duration than when I don't have the charisma gear on. Just personal experience.<P>I also have a little druid alt I hardly play, but I tried charm-fighting with her. She's a halfling, with 60 CHA. She couldn't keep a charm on an animal for more than a minute, even a green or low blue. My Enchanter alt, with 140 CHA, does significantly better.<P>I know many Enchanters have said that CHA doesn't have much effect on charming for them. (There are also those who feel the other way 'round.) But based on my own personal experiences and the testimony of others, I believe that for Bards (not Enchanters) CHA /does/ make a difference.<P>--------------------<P><A HREF="http://eq.castersrealm.com/players/view_profile.asp?Id=57639" TARGET=_blank>Devamaru Silverlight</A><BR>Torvonnilous
