<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
I have to agree with Tsunamii that charisma is highly overrated in terms of importance.  Comparing spells between classes is somewhat like comparing apples and oranges, but you'd have to figure there's some correlation in how bard songs and enchanter spells are meant to be influenced.  There are basically two things that impact how well you'll be able to stick your songs on the bad guys:  1) your level relative to that of your target, and 2) the natural resist rate of your target.  A level 26 bard is going to have a fair amount of resists when fighting goblin warlords or charbone skeletons in LOIO.  A level 30 bard will have a much lower resist rate.  Having 150 charisma may indeed impact your rate of resistance, but truly doubt the results will be that noticeable.  If you really want to test the theory, take a friend to the Arena and pixie strike him for an hour or so and record the number of sticks and resists using different levels of charisma.  My level 50 bard still only has 112 charisma, and he doesn't have any problem getting his songs to stick.
</FONT>
