now they are starting to have higher and higher HP's so they can take uber mob beatings for longer, etc.<P>Plus, higher AC = More MISS!  I know for a fact that the best way to channel is to not be hit at all, thats also the best way to survive, to not be hit.<P>If warriors all of a sudden gained the ability to charm do you think they would sacrifice all their AC/HP stuff so they could charm for long periods of time?  NO, they would charm lower level stuff that probably already hit the resist floor and keep whackin away in the thick of stuff with high AC/HP to keep them alive.<P>If any of you play on Rallos and want to do some tests feel free to /tell me.  Ill be (1) lvl higher than you and you can put on up to 255cha.  Then we will see who charms the same mob better.  Odds are you could gain a level or 2 in the time it takes you to get the cha items needed to get to 255.<P>Tinolan, who told you CHA helps in charming?  Why do you blindly believe them?  My enchanter had high cha and believe it or not got the same resists after I took off my cha stuff.  I never put it back on after that either and it hasnt made me any worse of an enchanter, if anything it made me better because I can take for at least 1-2 rounds average more than I could back then with more AC/HP.<P>I can also venture to guess WHY the bard community is behind the enchanter community when it comes to the CHA debate also.  Because enchanting gets SOO boring its not funny hell we cant mez or charm at high levels and have nothing better to do than sit there for 8 hours in OOT charming the same seafury cyclops over and over with different amounts of CHA.  Because people like Tudamorf who parse their logs to see the amount of resists in an entire night of fighting then record it and do it every day because they want to know how much difference CHA really makes.<P>Also This whole CHA idea came up as being useful back when STATS overall were useful.  Back when people made Ogre and Troll warriors and no warriors for other races because they only hit for 1/3 of the ogre/troll damage.  Back when enchanters could mez anything 6 levels higher with 255 cha and not ever get a resist.  Verant heard the cries of people who wanted change.  People who wanted to see halfling warriors and not having a whole army of 100 STR halflings try to equal the damage of a 200STR ogre.  Verant also didnt like how easy the game had become once mez became a commonly used spell and with zero resists became TOO overpowered.  They reduced the value of ALL stats to nearly zero value so that all class/race combinations COULD be played.  Wise move on verants part IMHO, I know a lot of people who would have got bored of ONLY seeing high elf enchanters and ONLY seeing erudite wiz and ONLY seeing ogre warriors.  Because of min/maxing thats the way it would be too and if someone played a halfling warrior they would suck and nobody would group with them when they could have a warrior and kill more things and get more EXP.<P>Think about that stuff for a while then go try with no +cha items and as many -cha items you can find.  You will be pleasantly surprised I almost guarantee you.<P>Tsunamii Starshine<BR>52 Enchantress Rallos Zek<BR>Breakdancer Tsunamii<BR>29 Bard Rallos Zek<P>--------------------<P>Tsunamii Starshine
