Tsunamii,<P>I have been in Sol B without any casters and it was still working fine in the high 40's.  The kill them fast, stop damage, heal damage works fine even then.  I think it was a warrior, rogue, 2 monks, a ranger and me.  Haste, Shield of Song, and Hymn were the songs that I was playing with a lute equipped.  <P>The pull rate was extremely fast, as was the kill rate, I would mez extras to allow the melees to concentrate on one target.  Ironically, since I was the group leader, when a monk needed to go, I recruited a rogue while there was a cleric looking for group.  I am still not sure why this pissed people off, but one of the group members recruited the cleric, and both the rogue and cleric showed up.<P>Needless to say, an argument followed, and I left the group under pressure because I would not invite the cleric.<P>Using similar tactics a few levels later in Karnor's Castle, (this time it was four melees, a cleric, and me) the cleric was so bored that he was nuking.<P>As a side note, I generated my character thinking that he would be a melee god.  Ummm, I was a newb and knew nothing at the time about bards, so it seemed logical.  I put all of my points into strength.  I played the high charisma game for a while, but lately have just been concentrating on ac and hps.<P>What I have found (keep in mind that this is totally unscientific and based on my experiences instead of hard data) is that two things matter most in terms of success.  <P>First, my level.  Mobs that would give me trouble last level, will often be easier to control one level later.  I am sure that this does not surprise anyone.<P>Second, the song used makes a difference.  Song of Twilight is much more effective than mezzes from previous levels.  I have loaded the old mez by mistake before, and it seems to be nowhere near as effective as Twilight.<P>Dilbis Xll &lt;Balefire Clan&gt;<BR>54th Huamn Bard<BR>Tarew Marr<P>P.S.  My charisma hangs out most of the time in the low 100's usually 101-103.<P>P.P.S.  My strength hangs out near 130 most of the time.  This gives me a plunder capacity of nearly 50 stone.  I will always carry out my share of FS, and when group members are looting it and dropping it, I will carry out their share, too.
