I never meant to imply that charisma was useless Tinolan.  My point is that I've made due with much less than many bards will tell you is "necessary" and I've never had a problem doing it.  I've killed 5 spirocs at once using charm, mez, snare and fear together when the rest of my group was OOM (bleh... all caster groups).  I've mezzed even cons at level 50 for minutes at a time while my hunting partner ran AFK to take a phone call...  and I've never had more than 112 charisma.  I've no doubt that a higher amount may reduce the number of resists I get - but frankly, the extra 250 hit points I have means more to me since my crowd control works fine as is.  The extra AC/HP gear I'm wearing could well be the difference between having time for a complete heal to land and sitting in Freeport again.  To me it's more than a worthy trade off for a mere percentage improvement on a facet of my game I'm already more than capable of doing.<P>As a side note to Torry... I'm afraid you couldn't be more wrong about classes balancing out.  This game is all about the melee classes on the higher end and many casters wind up feeling more and more useless as they rise in level.  I think when you've spent a little more time in the Planes and places like ToV you'll see that first hand.  Until then, I guess you'll just need to take the advice from the expertise way up there.<P>Walolen<BR>L50 Bard (Luclin)
