Unfortunately it's more than just raids Torry : (  Unless you're a Necro or Mage, you can pretty much forget about killing most things that /con higher than 45 or so with any sort of efficiency...  To give you an idea how skewwed things are, think of how much mana most casters would have to burn and med back up when fighting something like a frost giant elite or froglock forager/hunter.  Both are level 45 and both have on the order of 7,000 hit points.  For my rogue partner and I, these things may take a minute or maybe a tad longer to kill with maybe 30 seconds of healing between pulls with just the two of us (both level 50 and neither of us have haste items).  Take two wizards or druids in the same situation and you're looking at a pretty bad situation in terms of efficiency.  Where we can always try and nab a couple haste items to improve our kill speed, the poor casters don't have the benefit of manastones anymore... About the only thing they can do is beg for clarity : (<P>Walolen<BR>L50 Bard (Luclin)
