First of all, I want to see some sources on all these "tests" that were done showing how lousy charisma is. Back your self up, sheeshy louisy. In fact, I think I saw a test on this board that showed high charisma indeed did have a fairly decent impact on resists. Maybe not the most amazing one, but I think enough to justify increasing charisma. The fact is, I believe verant isn't stupid. I'm willing to believe that stats aren't the most important thing, but I WILL NOT Believe they are worthless. In regard to noticing changes in charisma and stuff, I cant say whether or not I've noticed huge changes with or without stats, but then again I havent noticed any change in the damage I've taken with higher ac in melee! But no one says AC isnt important! <BR>    Finally, someone was talking about casters fighting giants and stuff. Sure, a pure caster group might not be able to take out giants withouth much efficiency. But imagine this, you are hacking away at the level 45 giant when the wizard lets loose a few dds taking away 30% of the monsters hps. You've just saved yourself a lot of time in killing the pesky giant, saving you hps and giving you a chance to get some more kills. And, last i checked, wizards ruled at higher levels. I dont know whats up with that
